# .trivyignore — CVE suppression list for Trivy scans
# Format: one CVE ID per line (e.g., CVE-2024-XXXXX)
# Optional expiry annotation:
#   CVE-2024-XXXXX  # expires: YYYY-MM-DD

# CVE-2026-40355 — krb5 (MIT Kerberos 5): DoS via NULL pointer dereference
# in NegoEx. Not exploitable in this image: we ship a Python LLM ticket
# solver — we do not run a Kerberos server, do not negotiate NegoEx, and
# the krb5 libraries are only present as transitive system deps that are
# never invoked. Trivy classifies as CRITICAL despite CVSS=medium; safe
# to suppress in our deployment model.
CVE-2026-40355  # expires: 2026-08-24
